description: [Reuters] - Canadian chemical company Canexus Corp, which rejected a hostile bid from Chemtrade Logistics Income Fund, confirmed on Tuesday that it is in talks with the company about a higher offer. Chemtrade, a supplier of industrial chemicals, has increased its takeover offer to C$1.65 per share, Canexus said in a statement. Canexus rebuffed a C$1.50-per-share unsolicited offer in October, saying the C$297.2 million bid undervalued the company.
